<subSubSection id="E59D6574FFFA647CFF20C57CA066FAC7" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AD3836FFFFFA647CFF20C57CA05EFBBF" blockId="17.[189,344,1114,1140]" box="[189,344,1114,1140]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="F6708193FFFA647CFF20C57CA05EFBBF" bold="true" box="[189,344,1114,1140]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFF20C57CA05EFBBF" bold="true" box="[189,344,1114,1140]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD3836FFFFFA647CFF20C5AFA066FAC7" blockId="17.[189,1399,1160,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
Known from the slope of the 
<collectingCountry id="D590766FFFFA647CFDA5C5AFA37DFB68" box="[568,635,1161,1187]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Japan</collectingCountry>
Trench (
<typeStatus id="723C885DFFFA647CFD73C5AFA224FB68" box="[750,802,1161,1187]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
locality), off northeastern Honshu (
<quantity id="6A7F9B1AFFFA647CFB7FC5AEA474FB68" box="[1250,1394,1160,1187]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="415.0" valueMax="480.0" valueMin="350.0">350–480 m</quantity>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C9164B0EFFFA647CFF20C58AA07FFB0D" author="Hasegawa K." box="[189,377,1196,1222]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" pagination="225 - 383" refId="ref11908" refString="Hasegawa K. 2009. Upper bathyal gastropods of the Pacific coast of northern Honshu, Japan, chiefly collected by R / V Wakataka-maru. In: Fujita T. (ed.) Deep - sea Fauna and Pollutants off Pacific Coast of Northern Japan. National Museum of Nature and Science Monographs 39: 225 - 383." type="journal article" year="2009">Hasegawa 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and Kurile-Kamchatka Trench. Bathymetric range: the lower continental plateau from 
<quantity id="6A7F9B1AFFFA647CFF20C5E9A001FB22" box="[189,263,1231,1257]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
down to abyssal depth of at least 
<quantity id="6A7F9B1AFFFA647CFD0BC5E9A3F4FB22" box="[662,754,1231,1257]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="2700.0">2700 m</quantity>
. Inhabiting muddy and silty bottoms (after 
<bibRefCitation id="C9164B0EFFFA647CFB6DC5E9A052FAC7" author="Fraussen K. &amp; Chino M." pageId="17" pageNumber="28" pagination="145 - 157" refId="ref11562" refString="Fraussen K. &amp; Chino M. 2009. The deep-water genera Bathybuccinum and Ovulatibuccinum Golikov &amp; Sirenko, 1988 (Gastropoda: Buccinidae) in Japan and adjacent waters, with description of three new species. Venus 67 (3 - 4): 145 - 157." type="journal article" year="2009">Fraussen &amp; Chino, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E59D6574FFFA647CFF20C412A279F9C2" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AD3836FFFFFA647CFF20C412A036FA85" blockId="17.[189,304,1332,1358]" box="[189,304,1332,1358]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="F6708193FFFA647CFF20C412A036FA85" bold="true" box="[189,304,1332,1358]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFF20C412A036FA85" bold="true" box="[189,304,1332,1358]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD3836FFFFFA647CFF20C444A279F9C2" blockId="17.[187,1399,1378,1545]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
After synonimization of 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFE74C444A3B3FAB7" authorityName="Golikov &amp; Sirenko" authorityYear="1988" box="[489,693,1378,1404]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Ovulatibuccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFE74C444A3B3FAB7" box="[489,693,1378,1404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Ovulatibuccinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFC9DC445A270FAB7" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[768,886,1379,1404]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Buccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFC9DC445A270FAB7" box="[768,886,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Buccinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the new combination 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFB17C445A0F7FA54" authority="(Fraussen &amp; Chino, 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Fraussen &amp; Chino" baseAuthorityYear="2009" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Buccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perlatum">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFB17C445A471FAB7" box="[1162,1399,1378,1404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Buccinum perlatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C9164B0EFFFA647CFF58C4A3A0EEFA54" author="Fraussen K. &amp; Chino M." box="[197,488,1413,1439]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" pagination="145 - 157" refId="ref11562" refString="Fraussen K. &amp; Chino M. 2009. The deep-water genera Bathybuccinum and Ovulatibuccinum Golikov &amp; Sirenko, 1988 (Gastropoda: Buccinidae) in Japan and adjacent waters, with description of three new species. Venus 67 (3 - 4): 145 - 157." type="journal article" year="2009">Fraussen &amp; Chino, 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is becoming the junior secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFBB5C4A0A1FFFA08" authority="Conrad, 1833" authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1833" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Buccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perlatum">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFBB5C4A0A417FA54" box="[1064,1297,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Buccinum perlatum</emphasis>
Conrad, 1833
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFEB1C48FA3A9FA08" authority="Kuster, 1858" authorityName="Kuster" authorityYear="1858" box="[300,687,1448,1475]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Buccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perlatum">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFEB1C48FA315FA09" box="[300,531,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Buccinum perlatum</emphasis>
Küster, 1858
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFD4EC48FA549FA08" authority="Melvill, 1895" authorityName="Melvill" authorityYear="1895" box="[723,1103,1448,1475]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pisaniidae" genus="Engina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFD4EC48FA2A0FA09" box="[723,934,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Engina natalensis</emphasis>
Melvill, 1895
</taxonomicName>
). Since there is no known available and potentially valid synonym, according to art. 60.3 of ICZN the name 
<taxonomicName id="6A874D7CFFFA647CFB13C4EBA471FA2D" authorityName="Kuster" authorityYear="1858" box="[1166,1399,1484,1510]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Buccinum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perlatum">
<emphasis id="9FF3EAEDFFFA647CFB13C4EBA471FA2D" box="[1166,1399,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Buccinum perlatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be replaced by a new substitute name proposed herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
